msIdentifier.repository: Kislak Center for Special Collections, Rare Books and Manuscripts

msContents.summary: Calendar, verses on the psalms, and order of refectory reading (15th century), with Directorium divini officii secundum usum Cisterciensium added in a 17th-century hand on paper.

msItem.title: Table, and calculations for the date of Easter, f. 8r
Ad te levavi populus and Quomodo hystoriae per annum cantatur, f. 9v
Notes (on medicine, agriculture) arranged according to the zodiac and the months of the year, f. 10r
Quo ordine libri in refectorio per annum legunter, f. 17r
Directorium divini officii secundum usum Cisterciensium, f. 123r

supportDesc.extent: 139 leaves : 165 x 122 (131 x 187) mm. bound to 185 x 128 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Parchment and paper, 139; [1-122], 1-17; 17th-century foliation in ink, upper right recto; modern foliation in pencil, upper right recto.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: First section written in a Gothic cursive script by a single hand; second section written in a 17th-century cursive script by a second hand. Some marginal annotations in later hands.

decoDesc.decoNote: Rubricated headings, capitals, initials, and paragraph marks.

origin.p: Written in Germany in the 15th century, with second section written in the 17th century (Zacour-Hirsch).
